<item>
            <title>[MGPG-26] sign-and-deploy-file does not work with javadoc and sources artifcats</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MGPG-26</link>
                <project id="12317521" key="MGPG">Maven GPG Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you are trying to deploy an Ant project with javadoc and sources the gpg plugin does not create the &quot;.asc&quot; appropriate file name for these types. Following is a snippet of Ant script that reproduce the issue.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;	&amp;lt;exec dir=&quot;.&quot; executable=&quot;${maven.executable}&quot; failonerror=&quot;true&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;gpg:sign-and-deploy-file&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-DartifactId=core-client&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-Dfile=core-client-javadoc.jar&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-DgeneratePom=false&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-DgroupId=com.yournamehere&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-Dgpg.keyname=${gpg.keyname}&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-Dpackaging=javadoc&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-Dgpg.passphrase=${gpg.passphrase}&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-DrepositoryId=${maven.repository.id}&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-Durl=${maven.url}&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;arg value=&quot;-Dversion=6.0.2&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;/exec&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  The result will be &quot;core-client-6.0.2-javadoc.javadoc.asc&quot; when the right result would be &quot;core-client-6.0.2-javadoc.jar.asc&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
